░▒▓██ User Authentication System
░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░

░▒▓█ B1: User Login
░▒▓ B1-D1: Trigger
  When user submits login form with email AND password

░▒▓ B1-D2: Preconditions
  - User account [exists]
  - Account is NOT locked
  - REQUIRED: valid email format

░▒▓ B1-D3: Input
  Input: `email` (string), `password` (string)
  Source: POST /api/auth/login

░▒▓ B1-D4: Processing
  - fetch user record by email
  - verify password hash
  - If credentials valid: create session token
  - If credentials invalid: log failed attempt
  On Failure: increment `failedAttempts` counter

░▒▓ B1-D5: Output
  Output: `{ token, expiresAt, user }` → client
  Status: 200 OK [true] or 401 Unauthorized [false]

░▒▓ B1-D6: Postconditions
░▒ Session token stored in `sessions` table
░ Last login timestamp updated

░▒▓ B1-D7: Error Handling
  BLOCKING: database connection failure
  SPEC ISSUE: token generation timeout not defined
  - If database unreachable: return 503
  - If token generation fails: retry 3 times, then FAIL

░▒▓ B1-D8: Logging
  INFO: login attempt for `email`
  ERROR: authentication failure — invalid credentials
  WARN: account approaching lockout threshold
  DEBUG: session token generated, expires at `expiresAt`

░▒▓ B1-D9: Side Effects
  - send welcome notification
  - update analytics dashboard
  - trigger session cleanup for expired tokens

░▒▓ B1-D10: Security
  - MUST rate-limit to 5 attempts per minute
  - SHALL hash passwords with bcrypt
  - NEVER log raw passwords
  - ALWAYS sanitize email input

░▒▓ B1-D11: Performance
  - Target: < 200ms response time
  - Database query MUST complete within 50ms
  - Token generation: ~10ms

░▒▓ B1-D12: Dependencies
  - B2-D4 (session management)
  - B3-D1 (notification service)
  - /src/auth/login.ts
  - $AUTH_SECRET environment variable

░▒▓ B1-D13: Testing
  PASS: valid credentials → 200 + token
  PASS: invalid password → 401 + error message
  FAIL: SQL injection in email field
  - test with expired accounts
  - verify lockout after 5 failed attempts ✓
  - verify rate limiting ✗

░▒▓ B1-D14: Edge Cases
  - Unless account is SSO-only: allow password login
  - While migration in progress: accept BOTH old AND new password hashes
  - For each active session: check OPTIONAL `deviceId` field
  - N/A for passwordless accounts

░▒▓ B1-D15: Notes
  Version: 2.3.0
  Extracted from neffflix project where it was developed AND battle-tested.
  For all questions → contact auth team
  "This behavior is critical path" — see B1-D10 for security requirements
